pointed out last week on the

00:07:39.500 --> 00:07:40.200
App Clinic.

00:07:40.200 --> 00:07:45.640
Recent searches is something
that's really commonly used.

00:07:45.640 --> 00:07:48.350
You don't want to lose something
you just did, right?

00:07:48.350 --> 00:07:49.990
So if you went into the app and
did a search, maybe you

00:07:49.990 --> 00:07:51.800
did another search, and you want
to go back to the other

00:07:51.800 --> 00:07:54.090
one, you really don't want to
have to rewrite everything or

00:07:54.090 --> 00:07:57.400
reenter all that information.

00:07:57.400 --> 00:07:58.770
NICK BUTCHER: Especially if
you've got a property like

00:07:58.770 --> 00:08:01.890
Kayak, which has that
rich web property.

