00:25:52.090 --> 00:25:54.610
In general, when designing with
photos, some folks may

00:25:54.610 --> 00:25:59.980
think, oh, my photo is a certain
aspect ratio, so the

00:25:59.980 --> 00:26:02.990
UI element also needs to
be that aspect ratio.

00:26:02.990 --> 00:26:05.100
Don't lock yourself
in that way.

00:26:05.100 --> 00:26:08.925
Especially for photos where the
subject is in the center,

00:26:08.925 --> 00:26:12.040
feel free to use something
called Center Crop, which is

00:26:12.040 --> 00:26:16.300
scale type on Image views, where
basically you select the

00:26:16.300 --> 00:26:20.390
aspect ratio, and the image is
cropped within the UI element.

00:26:20.390 --> 00:26:23.900
So you'll chop off either the
sides, the left and the right,

00:26:23.900 --> 00:26:26.550
or the top and the bottom to
make sure that the image

00:26:26.550 --> 00:26:29.610
itself maintains its aspect
ratio while fitting within the

00:26:29.610 --> 00:26:30.440
UI element.

00:26:30.440 --> 00:26:33.120
So I think this works really
well for things like avatars,

00:26:33.120 --> 00:26:35.500
like people avatars, where there
face is usually in the

00:26:35.500 --> 00:26:41.610
center and photos of Big
